<h1>P20 profile: </h1>
<h2>{{ country.longname }}</h2>
<p>Agenda 2030 includes the specific commitment to Leave No One Behind. Together with Sustainable Development Goal 10 to reduce inequality, this requires faster than average progress for the poorest. The test is whether the gap between the poorest 20% of people (the P20) and everyone else is reducing or getting wider.</p>
<p>The P20 Initiative uses data to show whether the poorest 20% of people are getting their fair share of attention, investment and opportunity. It uses three bellwether indicators of progress: income, nutrition and civil registration and it promotes all data being disaggregated by Income Quintile, Gender, Geography, Age and Disability.</p>
<p>This profile provides key available data about the status of the P20 in {{ country.sentencename }}.</p>

<h2>The P20 in {{ country.sentencename }}</h2>
{% if country.P20pop is not none %}
	<p>{{ country.P20pop|people }} people in {{ country.sentencename }} are among the poorest 20% of the world’s population – the global P20. That is {{ country.PercentinP20|percent }} of the total population and they live on less than $2.54 a day.</p>
	{% if country.PercentinP20>0 %}
		{% if country.minimumincome>2.54 %}
			<p>The national P20 – the poorest 20% of people within {{ country.sentencename }} – live on less than {{ country.MaximumIncomeConsumptionNP20|dollar }} a day compared with an average {{ country.NationalRestAverage|dollar }} for the rest of the population.<p>
		{% else %}
			<p>The national P20 – the poorest 20% of people within {{ country.sentencename }} – live on between {{ country.minimumincome|dollar }} and {{ country.MaximumIncomeConsumptionNP20|dollar }} a day compared with an average {{ country.NationalRestAverage|dollar }} for the rest of the population.</p>
		{% endif %}
	{% else %}
		<p>The national P20 – the poorest 20% of people within {{ country.sentencename }} – live on between {{ country.minimumincome|dollar }} and {{ country.MaximumIncomeConsumptionNP20|dollar }} a day compared with an average {{ country.NationalRestAverage|dollar }} for the rest of the population.</p>
	{% endif %}
{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="458" src="no_data.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}
<p><b>Source: </b>Development Initiatives based on PovcalNet<a href="#{{ country.slug }}1"><sup>1</sup></a></p>

<h2>Income</h2>
{% if country.gap_1999 is not none %}
	<p>In 1999 the gap between the national P20 and everyone else in {{ country.sentencename }} was {{ country.gap_1999|dollar }} and in 2013 it was {{ country.gap_2013|dollar }}.</p>
{% else %}
	{% if country.gap_2013 is not none %}
		<p>In 2013 the gap between the national P20 and everyone else in {{ country.sentencename }} was {{ country.gap_2013|dollar }}.</p>
	{% else %}
		<img width="1004" height="152" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
		<p><b>No data available</b></p>
	{% endif %}
{% endif %}
<h3>{{ country.name }} income trends</h3>
{{ country.c1 }}
<p><b>Source: </b>Development Initiatives based on PovcalNet</p>

<h2>Nutrition</h2>
<p>Nutrition is fundamental to the ability to learn and earn. Children who experience poor nutrition can suffer lifelong disadvantage as a result.</p>
{% if country.nationalstunting is not none %}
	{% if country.nationalP20stunting is not none %}
		<p>In {{ country.sentencename }}, {{ country.nationalstunting|percent }} of children under five years old experience stunting. In the national P20 {{ country.nationalP20stunting|percent }} experience stunting compared with {{ country.restP20stunting|percent }} of the rest of the population.</p>
	{% else %}
		<p>In {{ country.sentencename }}, {{ country.nationalstunting|percent }} of children under five years old experience stunting. It is not possible to disaggregate stunting rates between the national P20 and the rest of the population.</p>
	{% endif %}
{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="202" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}

<h3>Stunting in children in the P20 compared with rest of country</h3>
{{ country.c2 }}
<p><b>Source: </b>Development Initiatives based on UNICEF-WHO joint child malnutrition estimates<a href="#{{ country.slug }}2"><sup>2</sup></a></p>

<h2>Birth registration</h2>
<p>Civil Registration means people count and have rights. Worldwide around 71% of children are birth registered. If you are born into the poorest 20% of people you are much less likely to have your birth registered.</p>
{% if country.restreg is not none %}
	<p>In {{ country.sentencename }} {{ country.NP20Reg|percent }} of births in the national P20 are registered compared to {{ country.restreg|percent }} in the rest of the population.</p>
{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="152" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}

<h3>Birth registration rates for children under five</h3>
{{ country.c3 }}
{% if country.birthregtrends is not none %}
	<p>Birth registration rates in {{ country.sentencename }} have {{ country.birthregtrends }}.</p>
{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="152" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}
<p><b>Source: </b>Development Initiatives based on World Bank World Development Indicators: Completeness of birth registration %<a href="#{{ country.slug }}3"><sup>3</sup></a></p>

<h2>Education</h2>
<p>Education is fundamental to a person’s life chances. </p>
{% if country.SecondaryCompletion is not none %}
	<p>As of {{ country.nateducYear|year }}, {{ country.SecondaryCompletion|percent }} of people in {{ country.sentencename }} have completed secondary school education.</p>
{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="152" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}

<h3>percentage who have completed secondary education</h3>
{{ country.c4 }}
{% if country.secondarycompletionP20 is not none %}
