{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="152" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}

<h3>Secondary school completion rates </h3>
{{ country.c5 }}
<p><b>Source: </b>Demographic Health Surveys (DHS)</p>

<h2>Health</h2>
<p>Poor health plays a major part in keeping people in poverty. If you are among the P20 you are more likely to suffer from preventable diseases and to die earlier.</p>
{% if country.NtlUnder5Mortality is not none %}
	<p>In {{ country.sentencename }} the under-five mortality rate is {{ country.NtlUnder5Mortality|people }} per 1,000 live births.</p>
{% else %}
	<img width="1004" height="152" src="no_data_quarter.png"/>
	<p><b>No data available</b></p>
{% endif %}
{% if country.U5MortalityNP20 is not none %}
	<p>The under-five mortality rate among the P20 is {{ country.U5MortalityNP20|people }} per 1,000 live births compared with {{ country.U5MortalityRest|people }} per 1,000 live births for the rest of the population.</p>
{% else %}
	<p>Data is not available that allows us to disaggregate under-five mortality based on income and therefore we are unable to see this information for the P20 versus the rest of the population.</p>
{% endif %}

<h3>Under-five mortality rates</h3>
{{ country.c6 }}
<p><b>Source: </b>Development Initiatives based on Demographic Health Surveys (DHS)</p>
